  "texts": [
    "Accordingly, user studies seem inevitable in the evaluation of XAI, if the aim is to generate explanations that can support human decision making.",
    "However, recent findings from user studies have severely dampened the initial optimism about the usefulness of saliency maps.",
    "While they were often found to increase self-reported human trust in the AI, they did not actually improve human-AI collaboration (e.g., Kim et al., 2022).",
    "They were appealing but not useful when it comes to objective performance.",
    "In fact, they may even lead to characteristic biases due to misinterpretations of feature relevance (Balayn et al., 2022; Kim et al., 2018) or an uncritical agreement with incorrect AI predictions (Nguyen et al., 2021; Stock & Cisse, 2018)."
  ],
